==Indonesian==
===Etymology===
Malay ''makan'', from Proto-Malayic ''*makan'', derived from Proto-Malayo-Polynesian ''*kaen''.  Cognates include Tagalog ''[[kain]]'', Maori ''[[kai]]'', Hawaiian ''[['ai]]'' and Fijian ''[[kana]]''.

